{"author":{"id":"76c6247d895d000228867c3fe1300cb2379d43911f85e446c15168dda4d8195e"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1619680257,"nonce":"tCbBhdSsGCNiG9t0U5S/dZgBbMo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU4NzA2ODc1NzQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3641","origin":"github"},"title":"RNA STARsolo UI Mislabelling in Galaxy","message":"Hi folks,\n\nI've found what appears to be a misconfigured parameter in RNA STARsolo in the Galaxy implementation.\n\nWhen selecting the input parameters, under \"Reference genome with or without an annotation\", when \"use genome reference without builtin gene model\" is selected, the form displays \"Gene model (gff3,gtf) file for splice junctions\" with an input for a gene model file (see RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_1a.png and RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_1b.png). Similarly, when \"use genome reference with builtin gene model\" is selected, there is no way to enter a gene model file, as the option is not present (RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_2a.png and RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_2b.png).\n\n![RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_1a](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1300104/116513001-43f89b80-a90c-11eb-8302-0357538239c4.png)\n![RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_1b](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1300104/116513002-44913200-a90c-11eb-8bb8-f52aec9626e3.png)\n![RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_2a](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1300104/116513003-44913200-a90c-11eb-932a-24f59260cf7f.png)\n![RNA_STARsolo_UI_issue_2b](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1300104/116512994-42c76e80-a90c-11eb-8ddb-46d0fdd846bb.png)\n\nThe tool will not allow you to advance without a gene model being selected.\n\nUnsure if it should be it's own issue or rolled into this one: https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3540\n\nThanks,\n\n\nDarren","files":null}]}